      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "The workflow editor is where Bubble really earns its reputation. It's a visual programming language — and once you understand its logic, you can build almost anything a traditional coded app can do.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "h3",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "A Real Database, Not a Spreadsheet",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Some no-code tools treat your data like a Google Sheet. Bubble gives you a proper relational database. You define data types (like \"User,\" \"Order,\" \"Product\"), set field types (text, number, date, file, geographic address), and create relationships between them.",
            "marks": []
          }
