        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Who Is Bubble Ideal For?",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Bubble shines brightest for specific types of builders and projects:",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Startup Founders & Solopreneurs",
            "marks": [
              "strong"
            ]
          },
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": " who need to validate an idea fast. Instead of spending $15,000+ on a development agency or three months learning to code, you can build an MVP in weeks and start getting real user feedback.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "SaaS Builders",
            "marks": [
              "strong"
            ]
          },
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": " creating multi-tenant applications with user accounts, dashboards, and subscription billing. Bubble handles this use case exceptionally well — many successful SaaS products run entirely on Bubble.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Marketplace Creators",
            "marks": [
              "strong"
            ]
          },
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": " building two-sided platforms (think Airbnb-style or Upwork-style apps) where buyers and sellers interact, transact, and leave reviews.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Internal Tool Teams",
            "marks": [
              "strong"
            ]
          },
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": " who need custom dashboards, CRMs, or workflow tools that fit their exact process — not generic templates that require workarounds.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Agencies & Freelancers",
            "marks": [
              "strong"
            ]
          },
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": " who want to deliver apps to clients faster and at lower cost while still providing polished, professional results.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Non-Technical Product Managers",
            "marks": [
              "strong"
            ]
          },
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": " who understand their users deeply but can't write code. Bubble lets them build and iterate on features without waiting in a developer's queue.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "If you fall into any of these categories, Bubble is worth serious consideration. It won't replace custom code for every scenario — but for a huge range of web applications, it's the fastest path from idea to launched product.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
